snippet.textDisplay:
Forget about the whole ball hit the rim or lane violation etc.
The rule is simple here. Ref blows the whistle at 4:11 exactly while ball is still is Simmons' hands. So his shot is released after a ref call. So his shot CANNOT be counted in. That's NBA basics.
Whatever they decide about the ball hitting the rim or the lane violation, simmons' shot is after the call and so literally never existed. No continuation, nothing.

So the right calls all along that (crazy) play would be:
Ref blows whistle and stops the games to check if ball hit the rim. It did. So plays goes on. But for like .2 sec only. Until ref's call. Simmons' putback doesn't exist. Ball can't be given to Heat or sixers cause game stopped by ref's mistake = jumpball. With like 0.1 on the clock. Heat wins in regulation.


Note: If ref blows his whistle (to check if ball hit the rim) like .2 sec later, then the ball has been released by Simmons,
and this is how NBA rules play out in that (extremely rare) case:
Ball hit the rim so play goes on. And (let's say) ref blows whistle .1 sec after Simmons' release. So Simmons' shot is good right? ... Not so quick.
If you pause at 6:16 right before Josh releases the ball, you can see that both simmons and Meyers Leonard straddle their lane at the exact same time while the ball is still in the shooter's hand. That's 2 lane violations by both team and at the same time.
So right call imo is no call. Let it play. (cause can't call simultaneous lane violation against both teams... Unless you can and it's a jumpball but I doubt it.) And so Simmons' putback is good and so OT.

If Leonard doesn't straddle his lane or does it just .2sec later, then Simmons commits the first (and only) lane violation to be called. Ball to Heat with .1 sec left.. Heat wins in regulation.
I don't know what they ruled it in game (thanks BR for cutting the final call wtf) but it's very clear after 3 replays. Gonna check what they called it rn.


NBA if you read that, I'll take the job lol

snippet.textDisplay: I'm a Celtics fan, but the Heat has overall impressed me so much. Nobody ever thought that the Heat would be at the level that they're in, with the 3rd seed in the East so far, and I'm very proud of them. You got Jimmy Butler as a lethal scorer with Tyler Herro as one of the best steals in the draft, and you got Bam Adebayo that has improved his game so much and is a MIP candidate. As a Celtics fan, I might get heated for this, but good job for the Heat and their fans and I wish them all perfect success this season.
